The Chief of Staff to the President, Abba Kyari has confirmed at the Presidential Election Petitions Tribunal that there are no certificates attached to President Muhammadu Buhari’s documents for the February 23 presidential election. Kyari, who was testifying as the third defense witness to the president, admitted that the INEC Form CF001, containing the president’s bio data and his Curriculum Vitae only listed schools attended without the certificates obtained. While being cross examined by counsel to the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) and its candidate, Atiku Abubakar, Levy Uzoukwu (SAN), Kyari admitted that the Diploma in Strategic Studies, which was listed as obtained by the president from the United States War College was not attached in the documents. Kyari testified that he visited the University of Cambridge, UK to collect the Cambridge Assessment International Education Certificate of the president on July 18, 2019. He admitted that he obtained the document after deposing to his witness statement on oath in April, 2019. Under cross examination by INEC counsel, Yunus Ustaz Usman, SAN, Kyari said the president had always communicated in English language as Nigerian’s official language. A/Court reserves judgment in Buhari’s certificate case Presidential Tribunal: Buhari opens defence, calls Abba Kyari, 2 other witnesses Court strikes out cases against Buhari over certificate Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin